00:00:13.223 --> 00:00:16.560
Namaste! Welcome to Aha Yemi Ruchi!

00:00:26.655 --> 00:00:33.153
I'll be cooking Mutton Chops Masala

00:00:34.896 --> 00:00:38.128
Ingredients required to make Mutton Chops Masala

00:00:38.351 --> 00:00:43.323
Mutton Chops, Coconut, Mint Leaves, Onions, Green Chilli, Pepper

00:00:43.555 --> 00:00:47.869
Cardamom, Cloves, Salt &amp; Ginger-Garlic Paste

00:00:48.841 --> 00:00:52.665
Let's see how it's made

00:00:52.979 --> 00:00:58.803
Take a pan and heat some oil

00:00:59.955 --> 00:01:04.287
Add some green chillies (10 - 12 chillies for 1/2 kg mutton)

00:01:04.664 --> 00:01:10.868
Two spoons of pepper

00:01:15.869 --> 00:01:22.642
A few mint leaves and fry them

00:01:48.922 --> 00:01:53.970
Now, grind these fried ingredients into a paste

00:02:03.826 --> 00:02:08.454
Now, take a cooking pan and grease it with a little oil

00:02:10.068 --> 00:02:16.069
Add some chopped onions and fry them

00:02:16.573 --> 00:02:21.456
Then, add some ginger-garlic paste

00:02:22.096 --> 00:02:26.581
Few cloves and cardamom

00:02:27.840 --> 00:02:35.401
At the same time, add some chopped coconut to the ground paste
 and grind them together to make the masala paste

00:02:50.923 --> 00:02:58.441
Now, add the mutton chops into the cooking pan

00:03:01.556 --> 00:03:05.114
Add a little turmeric powder for color

00:03:13.803 --> 00:03:19.729
A little salt for taste

00:03:30.668 --> 00:03:37.231
Add the ground masala paste into the cooking pan

00:03:45.576 --> 00:03:55.687
Add a little water into the pan and cook for at least 12 - 15 minutes

00:04:04.620 --> 00:04:10.563
Take the mutton into a serving bowl

00:04:12.725 --> 00:04:19.406
Garnish with some coriander leaves and onions

